snack_taste_test: Taste test: You get a cheese taste at first, but after about three-quarters of a bite, the jalapeño taste kicks in.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: They smell like cheddar.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: They taste like Doritos.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: They smell like Cheese-Its.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: I like these.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: They smell like paprika, a bit barbecuey.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These taste just like the earlier, Cooler Ranch variety, but with the snazzy new packaging.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: A ranchy type of smell, typical Doritos.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: The revival of the Doritos 3D brand continues, as after a decade of being dormant, we've seen in the span of four months first a Jalapeño Pepper Jack version and now this Bacon Cheddar Ranch one. The snacks had the same shape as the other recent one, not pillow-like like the old days, but instead in some sort of triangular pattern.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: A lot going on. There was something in addition to the taste corn smell, but with bacon, cheddar and ranch all (in theory) crammed in there, I couldn't really smell any of them.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: For years, Doritos 3D's have been one of those snacks that lots of people wanted to eat, but nobody could find them. Over a decade ago, we reviewed Zesty Ranch, Jalapeño Cheddar and Nacho Cheesier versions from the USA and a Texas Paprika flavor from the UK. Since then, we've had numerous folks reading those reviews and trying to find them, with no success.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Kind of like ranch flavor, with maybe a bit of heat too.

snack_name: Doritos Mini 3D's Zesty Ranch Go Snacks
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are smaller triangular versions of 3D's with the same kind of ranch flavor as seen in the larger snack.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Pretty strong ranchy Dorito smell. Tingled the nose when I took a big whiff.

snack_name: Go Snacks Doritos Mini 3D's Nacho Cheesier
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are miniature versions of the 3D Nacho Cheesier snacks, there's a good amount of nacho cheese on each piece (very triangular, in fact), but not enough where you're going to get a lot of residue on your fingers.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: A slight cheese odor/aroma.

snack_name: Matutano Bugles 3D's Conas de Maíz/Cones de Milho Sabor a Queso y Bacon/Sabor a Queijo y Bacon
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are pretty much the Spanish/Portugese version of Bugles.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Good.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These hollow, uniformly shaped hexagonal processed potato snacks have a decent but not great barbecue taste.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smells like barbecue powder, nothing special.

snack_name: Ruffles 3D's Maximum Cheddar flavored potato snacks
snack_taste_test: Taste test: I wasn't that impressed by the taste of these.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Potato-based type smell, not too strong.

snack_name: Ruffles 3D's Supreme Sour Cream & Onion flavored potato snacks
snack_taste_test: Taste test: Like their new Flavor Rush brand of potato chips, there's too much powder on these potato puff snacks, which are shaped like checkered hexagons.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Strong oniony smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This candy bar has smooth, rich chocolate featuring little air bubbles, making it light yet satisfying for those chocolate lovers out there.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Chocolate-y.

snack_name: Nestle Aero 2 in 1 Bubbly Milk and White Chocolate
snack_taste_test: Taste test: This version of the Aero bar from Nestle's Polish division featured an all-milk-chocolate exterior arranged in six domed sections, each spanning the full width of the bar.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice mild chocolate smell, mix of white and milk.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: From the outside, these spherical candies had one pale green mint hemisphere and one light-colored milk chocolate hemisphere.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Great chocolate mint smell. Just like a good mint chocolate chip ice cream.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This bar was about half as narrow and twice as long as the regular Aero bars.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Great caramel and chocolate smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: After very much enjoying the milk chocolate and chocolate mint versions of Aero, I wanted to try this to see if they could apply the same magic to dark chocolate (which I'm generally not the biggest fan of).
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very nice sweet dark chocolate smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This is the mint version of Nestle's awesome all-chocolate Aero bar.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Good chocolatey mint smell, more mint than Chocolate, similar to those little Andes candies.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This seasonal candy followed the formula of Nestle's Aero Mint bar but was shaped like a face-on view of a rather cute lamb. The exterior was all milk chocolate, except for a small hint of the mint green showing through above the lamb's left eye.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice subtle chocolate mint smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: After very much enjoying the caramel version of Aero Mousse — one of the best candy bars ever — I was eager to see how this all-chocolate version would measure up.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Great chocolate smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This bar's unusual look was really nice, as it had a 2x4 section grid that gave each section a bubble-like shape with the Aero logo on top.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Really nice milk chocolate and caramel smell. Wow!

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This version of the Aero bar had a 2x5 grid of very gracefully curved domes, each bearing the Aero logo (complete with bubbles emerging from the O).
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Strong chocolate orange smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: Andy Capp makes (or at least eats) some awfully good fries, in every flavor they make.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: The bag smells like barbecue sauce — there's a great, sweet barbecue aroma.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: Slighly spicy, very hard to place the flavor.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smells likes steak marinade

snack_name: Andy Capp's Hot Chili Cheese Steak Fries
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These fries tasted like a spicy Dorito, but hotter.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very strong chili pepper taco seasoning smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are the hot version of the very popular Andy Capp's Pub Fries.
snack_smell_test: Online store: Buy Andy Capp's on Amazon #ad

snack_taste_test: Taste test: Andy Capp's Fries were one of the first snacks we reviewed when we started this crazy enterprise more than 18 years ago. While other brands have expanded into dozens or even 100+ flavors, flavor expansion hasn't been a big thing for Andy — the number of Andy Capp's varieties in our reviews never went beyond six. (The beloved Pub Fries were discontinued before we ever got started.) Now, finally, there's a seventh flavor!
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Strong ranch smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are good fries with a nice spicy salsa flavor. They're kind of hot, and there's a definite salsa aftertaste. The fries vary in both thickness and length, and they have a good crunch.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Not a strong aroma, but it does smell like salsa.

snack_name: Andy Capp's White Cheddar Cheese Steak Fries
snack_taste_test: Taste test: There are a thicker cut version of regular Andy Capp fries.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice aroma of white cheddar

snack_name: Anne's Hand Cooked Nantucket Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are OK but nothing great.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Kind of oily.

snack_name: Bachman All Natural Wheat & Honey Pretzelsnack
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These thick pretzel snacks were about two inches long, had a nice crunch, and tasted quite good.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Not really a honey or a wheat smell, but OK.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These don't taste a whole lot different than the regular Pretzel Stix, but there may be a slight amount of butter in the taste.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smells like pretzels.

snack_name: Bachman Butter Twist Brick Oven Flame Baked Pretzels
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These knotted pretzels were very large and fairly thick, with lots of salt crystals on their surfaces.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Strong pretzel smell, somewhat buttery.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are shaped like pretzel sticks, but they've used the dough from Cheez-Its or Cheese Nips or something along those lines to make them, then added salt just as with regular pretzels.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smells like pretzels.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are Bachman's version of Fritos.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smells like corn chips.

snack_name: Bachman Country Style Honey Mustard and Onion Sourdough Pretzel Pieces
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are really good.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: These smell great. You can smell all three flavors — honey, mustard and even the sweet onion. Nice.

snack_name: Bachman Golden Crisp All Natural Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are good conventional potato chips, very crisp with a rich potato flavor and not very much salt.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Regular potato chips smell.

snack_name: Bachman Golden Ridges Bar-B-Q Potato chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These narrow-rippled chips were very good.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice barbecue smell. Much different than most barbecue chips, not sweet at all.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These narrow-rippled potato chips were crisp with a soft crunch, on the salty side, and had lots of potato taste.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Not much.

snack_name: Bachman Golden Ridges Scorchers Red Hot Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These chips sure look hot.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smell like barbecue chips but with more intense flavor.

snack_name: Bachman Golden Ridges Sour Cream & Onion Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are average sour cream and onion chips.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Kind of oniony.

snack_name: Bachman Golden Ridges Vinegar Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: Very vinegary at first, but then the potato flavor comes through.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Vinegary.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are good pretzel bites.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Sourdough pretzel smell

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are your standard, round, salty tortilla chips.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smells like corn chips

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This is a very cheesy, salty and tasty party mix consisting of pretzel sticks, small knotted pretzels, Crunchy Jax, barbecue-flavored corn chips and nacho cheese tortilla chips.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Good cheesy smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These Pita Pretzel "Squares" were actually rectangular, measuring an inch in one dimension and a little over an inch in the other.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Similar to pretzels.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are your standard thin pretzel sticks, with a good crispness and a medium amount of salt.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very weak pretzels smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These pretzels were shaped kind of like puzzle pieces, with one flat side, one side opposite the flat side with one nub sticking out, and two sides with two nubs each.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: The usual pretzels smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These large knotted pretzels were indeed quite thin, and the shapes very nearly resembled hearts, with unusually pointy bottoms for knotted pretzels.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Strong pretzel smell. Good.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These round tortilla chips were thick and crunchy, with nearly all of the chips unbroken, though oddly, some of the had some small holes in them.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Not much. Maybe a little tortilla chips smell, but neither cheddar nor onion.

snack_name: Chipitos Salsa Tortilla Chips with Black Bean
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These tortilla chips were huge.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice, spicy tortilla chips smell. Smells like an entree at a Mexican restaurant.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These round tortilla chips were crisp but fairly brittle, so there were lots of broken pieces in the bag.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Just a regular tortilla chips smell. Can't smell any black pepper.

snack_name: Chipitos Sweet Chili Lime Tortilla Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These round tortilla chips were a somewhat dark shade of red, with some black spots and kind of a rough surface.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Mild but very nice chili and lime smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These round tortilla chips ranged from nearly flat to having a significant curl to them.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice tangy smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This was a special kind of pretzel designed for kids. They came in special shapes and were supposed to have some honey flavor. The taste was a bit different from regular pretzels, and that probably had something to do with the honey that has been added. However, there was quite a bit of salt too, which kind of neutralized the effect of the honey, so after eating a few, they really didn't taste much different from ordinary pretzels.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Sort of a honey aroma.

snack_name: Lay's Baked Cream, Herb & Onion Flavour
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These rippled potato crisps from India had irregular but loosely hexagonal shapes, with a pale yellow color overall but lots of bits of green stuff embedded inside. Yes, despite being Lay's and not Ruffles, did not have the flat surfaces of the American flavors of Baked Lay's.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice zesty mix of herbs.

snack_name: Lay's Baked KC Masterpiece Barbecue Flavor Potato Crisps
snack_taste_test: Taste test: Baked Lay's are "crisps" made from dehydrated potatoes, molded into a roughly hexagonal shape.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smells like barbecue sauce.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are kind of salty, not greasy at all (heck, they're baked!).
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very mild aroma, sort of like Pringles.

snack_name: Lay's Baked Sour Cream & Onion Potato Crisps
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are good, crunchy and not greasy snacks.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Slight onion aroma.

snack_name: Lay's Light & Baked Yuzu & Black Pepper Flavor
snack_taste_test: Taste test: This snack from China had roughly hexagonal shapes that were generally flat, much like the American versions of Baked Lay's, with a light smattering of dark seasoning bits on the surfaces.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Not really peppery like most black pepper snacks, but definitely something sharp and interesting.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These cheese balls weren't actually shaped like spheres, but more like short tubes with rounded ends.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very nice cheddar cheese smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These cheese puffs were thinner than the standard Jax chees puffs, with a good helping of fluorescent orange cheese powder.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice but mild cheddar cheese smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These cheese puffs were shaped like slightly oversized Cheerios, so they were quite a bit smaller than your usual cheese puff.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Barely any. Just the slightest cheese puff smell.

snack_name: Barrel o' Fun CornSations Nacho Cheese
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These hollow snacks were shaped kind of like penne pasta, except sort of flattened and generally curved.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Mild cheese smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These snacks were shaped kind of like penne pasta, except sort of flattened, with a mesh-like surface and a light yellow color.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Same as Bugles. Nice.

snack_name: Barrel o' Fun Gardy's Signature Flavors Baby Back Ribs Wavy Ripple Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These rippled potato chips were part of a new line of flavors inspired by Minnesota Twins manager Ron Gardenhire. The ripples were wide but not particularly high or sharp, and the chips were fairly thick and had a light yellow color with some orange seasoning plus some scattered bits of a darker orange. There were also some bits of skin on the edges. Chip sizes varied a lot, but there were some nice large pieces near the top of the bag.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Intense barbecue sauce smell. With some kick!

snack_name: Barrel o' Fun Gardy's Signature Flavors Cheddar & Horseradish Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips were somewhat wiggly and had a yellow/orange glow, with some scattered areas of dark skin on the edges of some chips, plus some bubbles embedded inside.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smells like potato and sour cream. Wouldn't know there was any horseradish.

snack_name: Barrel o' Fun Gardy's Signature Flavors Pickle Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips had somewhat wiggly surfaces, with some bits of skin along the edges, many tiny bubbles embedded inside, dark spots on some chips, and most notably, lots and lots of dill stuck to the otherwise bright yellow surfaces.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Strong pickle smell, like you've just opened a new jar of pickles.

snack_name: Barrel o' Fun Nacho Tortillas Nacho Cheese
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These triangular tortilla chips claimed on the bag to have a lot of cheese, and they did indeed have a lot of cheese.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very strong nacho cheese smell. Wow.

snack_name: Barrel o' Fun Old Fashioned Potato Chips 40% Reduced Fat Thick Cut
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These kettle-cooked potato chips were very crunchy, and they had a good helping of potato taste, with no taste that we could notice sacraficed in the name of having less fat.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: The usual smell of kettle-cooked potato chips, potaotey but somewhat oily.

snack_name: Barrel o' Fun Original Corn Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These corn chips were in the same category as your standard Fritos, but they were different in several ways.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Medium-strength corn chips smell.

snack_name: Barrel o' Fun Original Thin Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These conventional potato chips were very crisp and not the least bit greasy.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Wow, very, very nice potato chips smell. Not greasy, just potatoey. Wow.

snack_name: Barrel o' Fun Special Edition Flavor Dill Pickle Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: Guest reviewer Adam Kay reports: "Tastes like a mild salt and vinegar chip with a hint of dill.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smells like wicker furniture and dill ... but mostly like wicker.

snack_name: Boulder Canyon Authentic Foods Pumpkin Pie Flavored Kettle Cooked Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips, introduced along with a Turkey & Gravy flavor, had generally a golden yellow color, with the same wiggly shapes, bubbles and folded-over chips typical of kettle-cooked chips. There was no visible seasoning on the surfaces.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Not that strong, but it really did smell like pumpkin pie.

snack_name: Boulder Canyon Authentic Foods Turkey & Gravy Flavored Kettle Cooked Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: Turkey-flavored potato chips are quite the rarity, as we hadn't seen't found anything flavored with Thanksgiving's favorite meat since almost 13 years ago, when one of our chip hunters brought a bag of Lay's Turkey flavor back from China.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Wow, definitely smells like gravy, and maybe even a hint of turkey too.

snack_name: Boulder Canyon Balsamic Vinegar & Rosemary Kettle Cooked Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These kettle-cooked chips were really, really crunchy, with an olive oil-like taste.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: I could smell the tang of the vinegar, but the rosemary didn't come immediately to the senses. Another tester suggested "it smells like the roasted red bliss potatoes that you usually get with a chicken dinner."

snack_name: Boulder Canyon Natural Foods Avocado Oil Canyon Cut Kettle Cooked Potato Chips Sea Salt
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips had wide, shallow ripples, with generally a light yellow color but also some areas with minor browning, plus areas of skin on some edges.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Good mild fried potato smell.

snack_name: Boulder Canyon Natural Foods Baked Sweet Potato Fries Lightly Salted
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These fries were fairly thin, about the same width as most fast food fries, and most pieces were straight as an arrow, with a fairly typical sweet potato color, plus some bits of salt visible.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Not much. Just a slight, slight hint of sweet potato.

snack_name: Boulder Canyon Natural Foods Hickory Barbeque Kettle Cooked Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips had wiggly, irregular shapes, some large bubbles and a light orange overall color, as the golden yellow chips had some browning and dark orange seasoning.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very nice smoky hickory smell.

snack_name: Boulder Canyon Natural Foods Jalapeno Cheddar Kettle Cooked Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips had wiggly, irregular shapes and a light yellow color with some browning, some skin on the edges, plus a few bits of green seasoning.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Quite nice, though mild, mix of cheese and potato. Not much in the way of jalapeño.

snack_name: Boulder Canyon Natural Foods Limón Kettle Cooked Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips had a strong yellow color, with wiggly shapes, many folded-over chips and lots of skin around the edges.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Just mildly citrusy.

snack_name: Boulder Canyon Natural Foods Olive Oil Kettle Cooked Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips had generally somewhat wiggly or folded-over shapes, with surface colors ranging from light yellow to golden yellow, plus a lot of skin around the edges.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very nice rich potato smell.

snack_name: Boulder Canyon Natural Foods Spinach & Artichoke Kettle Cooked Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: When I saw this new flavor of chips, I knew that I had to buy it but doubted that I would like the taste (as I'm something of an anti-veggite).
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice mix of spices and veggies.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are good kettle-style chips.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Mild garlicy smell

snack_name: Boulder Malt Vinegar and Sea Salt Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are very flavorful chips, with a clean potato taste, crisp vinegar bite, and a fine balance of salt.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Malt vinegar, potatoes, a little scent of heaven.

snack_name: Boulder Potato Company Four Onion Intense Potato Chips!
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are thick, kettle-style chips with a good crunch.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very mild onion aroma.

snack_name: Boulder Potato Company Habanero Intense Potato Chips!
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are fairly hot chips.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: A hot smell, pretty good. Makes your mouth water.

snack_name: Boulder Potato Company Hickory Barbecue Intense Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: First off, I was very disappointed to open a bag and find it half full, the rest filled with air.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Pretty strong spicy barbecue aroma.

snack_name: Boulder Potato Company Jalapeño Cheddar Intense Potato Chips!
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are very crunchy kettle-style chips with a generous portion of flavor seasoning on them.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice mild jalapeno aroma.

snack_name: Boulder Potato Company Malt Vinegar & Sea Salt Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are good vinegar chips, with the crisp, kettle-cooked style that other Boulder chips have.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Strong vinegar zing.

snack_name: Boulder Potato Company Zesty Ranch Intense Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: Not a good taste.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Not a good smell. Smells nothing like ranch. Smells like moth balls.

snack_name: Boulder Sea Salt & Cracked Pepper Intense Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: This was another bag I bought in NYC for $3.59, only to find it half full (5 oz.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: A pretty good peppery smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are really good chips.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice spicy Thai food aroma.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: Clean potato taste, a bit of salt, and a hint of slightly rancid grease in the back of the palate.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Potatoes, natural potatoes.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This version of Bugles had a lots of seasoning on the exteriors of the brass instrument-shaped snacks, mostly orange stuff but with some darker bits as well.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Strong, sweet and tangy barbecue smell. Nice.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: Not bad.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Open a bag of taco seasoning mix (Ortega, Old El Paso), and that's what these smell like.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These Bugles are covered with a lot of powder, and it tastes like Bugles covered in taco powder.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smells like the taco powder you put onto burger if you're making homemade tacos.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These taste like regular Bugles, there's not much flavor at all on the snack.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: They smell like Old El Paso Taco powder.

snack_name: Bugles Nacho Cheese Flavor Crispy Corn Snacks
snack_taste_test: Taste test: Pretty good cheese flavor, not necessarily nacho cheese like Doritos but more of a cheese flavor you'd find in a Cheeto or Chex Mix.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Cheese smell.

snack_name: Bugles Old El Paso Salsa Crispy Corn Snacks
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are Bugles that taste like you had just dipped them into a jar of salsa.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: There's an aroma there, but hard to place. Doesn't smell like Mexican food or anything.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: It's hard to say what Bugles really are, but once you've eaten one, you really can't stop eating them until you've finished the bag.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: OK, maybe slightly oily smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: If you like salt and vinegar snacks, or if you like Bugles, then you'll like these.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: An odd vinegar aroma.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are good.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: I don't like the smell that much. After a couple of sniffs, it smells like Bugles. Better than regular Bugles.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: We've reviewed a number of varieties of Bugles, plus even more kinds of Cheetos, but this was the first time that we've seen a bag that was branded with both of them.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Mild shrimp smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are Bugles.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nothing significant on the smell side.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: Imagine taking regular corn Bugles and then slathering them with caramel as you do with caramel popcorn.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Slight caramel aroma, but not very powerful.

snack_name: Sweet & Salty Bugles Chocolate Peanut Butter
snack_taste_test: Taste test: This special flavor of Bugles had a fairly dark coating (darker than pictured on the bag) of chocolate and peanut butter, with a powdery exterior.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Wow, just amazing. Really rich mix of peanut butter and chocolate.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These Bugles looked much like the other flavors in terms of shape and color, but some of the pieces appeared to have some dark areas of cinnamon within the ridges encircling each piece.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Strong cinnamon sugar smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: Bugles might suffer from under-marketing these days, because for just about every person we shared this bag with, the reaction was, wow, I haven't eaten Bugles in forever, in many cases recalling that Bugles came in boxes rather than bags way back when.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice corn and ranch seasoning smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This British version of the corn-based Bugles had similar instrument-themed shapes and woven-looking surfaces as the other kinds we've tried, but in this case the cone shapes were generally flattened a bit. They had a yellowish color, plus a more orange look in areas with more seasoning powder.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Intense sharp nacho cheese smell, much like Doritos, very nice.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This version of Bugles had the same flattened bugles shapes as Walkers' cheese version, with a mild orange glow from a light coating of seasoning.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Great BBQ smell, like you just opened up a jar of your favorite sauce.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These thin, somewhat curvy fries had a light covering of bright orange seasoning with just a few green specks on each fry.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Mild cheesy flavor, cheddary but a bit odd.

snack_name: Burger King Flame Broiled Flavored Potato Snacks
snack_taste_test: Taste test: The Burger King branding on this snack turned a few heads around the chip bowl, but the "Flame Broiled" flavor label had most of our tasters wondering what that was supposed to mean.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Not a whole lot. Just some very mild spices.

snack_name: Burger King French Toast Flavored Snacks
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These corn meal-based snacks looked sort of like flattened cheese puffs, except with a color more like French toast.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smells like french toast with syrup. Pretty good.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These fries had the same shape as the Burger King Cheesy Fries, which is to say that neither one much resembled actual Burger King fries, as they were more like the various veggie potato stick snacks, with a much blander texture than I would want from a Burger King product.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Not good. Bad.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: The snacks in this bag of Burger King-branded potato crisps had a shape all their own, as they weren't shaped like fries, potato chips, potato sticks or anything else we've eaten.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Good tangy ketchup smell, similar to many ketchup potato chips.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: I was expecting this snack to be just another Funyuns clone with Burger King branding, but it turned out to be quite different.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very mild fried onion smell.

snack_name: Angela Marie's Crispy Marshmallow Goodie Made with Nestle Butterfinger
snack_taste_test: Taste test: This large rectangle of non-Kellogg's-brand Rice Krispies Treat was about an inch thick, a bit under 4 inches in one dimension and a bit over 4 in the other. It looked mostly like a regular Rice Krispies Treat, except for a very sparse smattering of tiny orange bits.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Mild, but it really does smell like Butterfinger

snack_taste_test: Taste test: When I recently reviewed skull-shaped Butterfinger peanut butter cups, I was quite impressed by the design and manufacturing craftsmanship in making the impressive shapes. I can't praise the Butterfinger team the same way for this one.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Good peanut buttery Butterfinger smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This version of Butterfinger included two bars, in the same end-to-end arrangement as the regular King Size package, but these bars were loaded up with extra caffeine.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Same as a regular Butterfinger.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: The four eggs in this package each had a milk chocolate shell filled with a sugary peanut butter creme with some pieces of Butterfinger mixed in.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very nice chocolate smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This candy bar had seven thin layers inside it: three Butterfinger layers interlaced among four chocolate wafer layers.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Kind of like a Butterfinger, but maybe weaker.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: When I opened the wrapper, I knew that they had replaced Butterfinger's usual milk chocolate coating with dark chocolate, but I was still a bit surprised by the look of a dark chocolate-coated Butterfinger. I crunched in to find the expected strong Butterfinger crunch, with lots of the delicious peanut butter center, complemented nicely by the dark chocolate. I'm generally a huge milk chocolate fan and not a dark chocolate fan, but in this case, the dark chocolate really worked well in a Butterfinger. Very good!
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Mostly lie a Butterfinger, but I could notice the dark chocolate.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: Butterfinger meets Reese's? We've tried many variations of Butterfinger but we can't think of any that created as much excitement and anticipation as this. We opened the wrapper and immediately were stuck by two major changes from Reese's (and their various imitators): 1) The cups were not round, but instead were squares, with rounded corners. 2) There was no wax paper cup enclosing each one.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smells like Butterfinger.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This special Easter candy was shaped like an egg chopped in half, with milk chocolate on the exterior surfaces and some Easter-like decorations indented into the curved side.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Just like Butterfinger

snack_name: Butterfinger Peanut Butter Cups Minis Unwrapped
snack_taste_test: Taste test: Having enjoyed the original, full size Butterfinger Peanut Butter Cups quite a lot, we figured we'd give this miniaturized version a try.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smells like a Butterfinger bar. Nice.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: I don't know whether the credit goes to the people of Nestle's Butterfinger Development Lab (I don't know any of them, or even if there really is such an institution), or the brand's marketing association with The Simpsons, of if maybe they have oompa loompas doing their good work — but somehow Butterfinger seems to be getting everything right lately.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Same as a Butterfinger bar. Nice!

snack_name: Butterfinger Pieces in Milk Chocolate Solid Bunny
snack_taste_test: Taste test: This chocolate bunny weighed in at an impressive 6+ ounces, and even more impressive, it was an inch thick at its thickest part.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Good Nestle chocolate smell. Not really any Butterfinger smell, though.

snack_name: Butterfinger Santa Claus is Comin' to Town
snack_taste_test: Taste test: This candy was shaped like an oversized coin, just under 3 inches in diameter, with Santa's face, some snowflakes and the words "Santa Claus is Comin' to Town" all protruding from the top of the coin. The surface was mostly milk chocolate, but there were some light bits of embedded Butterfinger that were vaguely poking through the surface.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smells like a mix of Butterfinger and milk chocolate.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This small bag contained 10 thin, sort of nugget-shaped candies, each with a milk chocolate exterior (kind of like a Butterfinger bar) with a peanut butter squiggle on top (unlike a Butterfinger bar).
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smells like a Butterfinger bar, very good.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These individually wrapped round-profile candy sticks were about 4-1/2 inches long and half an inch in diameter.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smells like a Butterfinger. Nice.

snack_name: Nestle Butterfinger Pieces in Milk Chocolate
snack_taste_test: Taste test: After being disappointed by the Butterfinger Pieces in Milk Chocolate Solid Bunny (not enough Butterfinger, almost entirely milk chocolate), I wasn't expecting much from this, as I figured it would be primarily a chocolate bar with minimal Butterfinger embedded inside the extra-large candy bar.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Good milk chocolate smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These actually do taste like Butterfinger candy, with a sweet and slight peanut butter taste.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Pretty strong peanut butter (or Butterfinger candy if you prefer) smell.

snack_name: Utz Mini Pretzels Covered with Butterfinger Candy Pieces
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These midsize knotted pretzels had a light colored coating, with tiny bits of crushed Butterfinger interior stuck to that. The crushed Butterfinger layer seemed far less generous on the actual pretzels than in the ones pictured on the bag. The color was overall kind of a light brown, not the bright orange that I usually associate with a Butterfinger bar. The mystery here was whether the first coating was chocolate or peanut butter. It looked too light to be milk chocolate, and the bag had three separate ingredient lists — Nestlé Peanut Butter Flavored Coating, Pretzel, and Nestlé Butterfinger Topping — none of which seemed to indicate chocolate.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smells like a Butterfinger bar.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This bar from India had a very similar composition to Nestlé's Bar One, both consisting of nougat and caramel, coated in milk chocolate. This Cadbury version was bigger than the Nestlé one, as it was much thicker, as well as wider and longer. It was on OK bar, better than the Nestlé one, but still just kind of bland, heavy on the nougat.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Chocolate and caramel, pretty good.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This candy bar had a nearly round profile, except that the bottom of the bar was flat, with a milk chocolate coating over the entire outside.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice chocolate smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This dark chocolate bar was broken lengthwise into six sections.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Typical dark chocolate smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This bar had a chocolate coating on all sides except the top, where you could see Rice Krispies and other cereal, plus raisins and oats.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Good Cadbury chocolate smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This bag contained a whole bunch of small, round, flat chocolatey treats. Each was about 3/4 inch in diameter (which I'm sure the British would prefer that we measure in millimetres), flat on the bottom and rounded on top. Kind of like nonpareils, but without the white specks. Upon careful examination, I noticed that the Cadbury logo was embossed on the bottom.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very nice milk chocolate smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This candy Easter egg had a thick milk chocolate shell, filled with a liquidy caramel.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Great chocolate and caramel smell. Mmmm.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This fairly large candy bar had a 5x2 grid of detachable sections, each bearing the Cadbury logo and with sort of a pillow shape on top.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very nice mild milk chocolate and caramel smell. Mmmmm!

snack_taste_test: Taste test: It was a bit tough to break off sections of this candy bar cleanly, and this is one of those bars where doing so is critical, because if you don't get a clean break, you risk breaching one of the caramel holding areas and making a mess of liquidy caramel.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Good caramel and chocolate smell. Sharp.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This thin, narrow candy bar had a caramel center and a chocolate coating.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very, very nice chocolate and caramel smell. Great.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This annual egg-shaped treat had a thick milk chocolate shell, with a sugary cream white inside.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very good chocolate smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: We all know what Cadbury Creme Eggs are, but what the heck is a Creme Egg Biscuit? The package contained a tray holding three stacks of two round cookies each, with flat bottoms, slightly domed tops and milk chocolate exteriors. So they didn't really look anything like Creme Eggs.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very nice chocolate smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: The idea here was to take the formula for a Cadbury Creme Egg but make it into a bar instead of an egg.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very nice milk chocolate smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This candy bar reminded me a lot of Butterfinger, as it had a chocolate exterior and a solid, flaky, crunchy interior made from peanuts.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Good peanuts and milk chocolate smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This candy bar had a honeycomb inside, basically a yellowish orange crunchy, hardened light foam, with a fairly thick chocolate coating on the outside.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very sharp chocolate smell. Not sure if I like it.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This was one of the most innovative and oddest candy bars I've ever tried. Inside the chocolate coating, the small bar seemed to contain four things: bits of the same honeycomb that you would expect from a Crunchie; Rice Krispies; Pop Rocks; and milk chocolate holding the first three things together.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Mild chocolate smell, nothing special.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: I've long been a fan of the Crunchie Bar, which combines a light but very crunchy (hence the name!) honeycomb interior with a thick milk chocolate coating for an experience that you just have to try to understand how good it is. This spinoff product promised clusters of milk chocolate with bits of that same honeycomb, plus corn flakes cereal, embedded inside.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Good milk chocolate smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This very thin candy bar was an inch wide and more than 7 inches long, with a series of eight holes spanning the length of the bar, each roughly trianglar and pointing toward the middle from alternating sides.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Good milk chocolate smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This candy bar was thick and rich, with a very good milk chocolate taste.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice milk chocolate smell.

snack_name: Cadbury Dairy Milk Bunny filled with a Chocolate Truffle Center
snack_taste_test: Taste test: This thall, thin candy bar was shaped like a bunny, with a thick chocolate shell and a generous chocolate truffle filling.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Bitter chocolate smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This large bar had a 6x3 grid of highly elevated sections, with a diagonal Cadbury logo atop each section, promising a caramel filling inside each one. When I broke off a row of three sections, I could tell by how easily it broke off that the milk chocolate was soft. It was also a nice clean break, with no caramel filling spilling out anywhere.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Just an awesome mix of milk chocolate and caramel. The best!

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These large, button-shaped candies each had a milk chocolate exterior, with a flat bottom bearing a pattern of Cadbury logos, a rounded top, and best of all, liquidy caramel filling the inside of each Nibble.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: very nice caramel and chocolate smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This box contained three small, clear bags with six small, frog face-shaped chocolates in two of the bags and seven of them in the third. The version of Freddo shown on the box was sticking his tongue out at me, but the actual candies included several different expressions (all of them quite expressive).
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice, like other Cadbury chocolates.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This candy bar had 8 rectangular (and very nearly square) sections in a 2x4 grid. Each looked like milk chocolate from the top, but you could see some of the pieces of honeycomb jutting out the bottom. More honeycomb pieces were scattered throughout the interior, though in total it was still overwhelmingly milk chocolate.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: OK chocolate smell, but not great.

snack_name: Cadbury Dairy Milk Little Robins Daim
snack_taste_test: Taste test: This small bag contained foil-wrapped chocolate eggs, with colorful wrappers similar to the designs on the bag. These eggs were way smaller than your typical Cadbury Creme Egg. The exterior of the chocolate had a small Cadbury logo, some stars and lines that went all the way around the egg.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Wow, really nice!

snack_name: Cadbury Dairy Milk Marvellous Creations Jelly Popping Candy
snack_taste_test: Taste test: This chocolate bar shared the same unusual shape and branding as the Rocky Mallow Road version, but it turned out to be an even odder one!
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very nice milk chocolate smell, just slightly fruity.

snack_name: Cadbury Dairy Milk Marvellous Creations Rocky Mallow Road
snack_taste_test: Taste test: This fairly thick bar had five whimsically shaped sections, with a different surface texture on each one.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Fairly strong strawberry smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This fairly large bar had a 4x2 grid of thick rectangular sections, with the Cadbury logo atop each and some chunky-looking bits (presumably the embedded mint crisp) jutting out of the bottom.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice chocolate mint smell, like Girl Scouts Thin Mints.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This chocolate bar had seven domed sections with a nice curvy appearance. Atop each section was neither a Cadbury logo nor an Oreo one, but instead some squiggly lines that vaguely resembled the "Dynamic Ribbon" from Coke's logo. From the outside, the surface looked mostly like milk chocolate, but there were a few darker areas that we figured came from the Oreo bits within.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Good chocolate smell, but couldn't really notice any Oreo.

snack_name: Cadbury Dairy Milk Ritz Moreish Crackers
snack_taste_test: Taste test: This rectangular chocolate bar had four sections in a 2x2 grid, each with something we've never seen in a candy bar: each section had a small rectangular Ritz cracker embedded inside. A cracker could also be seen on the bottom surface of each section. The initial mystery was whether the crackers on the top and bottom were in fact the same cracker. We crunched in to solve this mystery, and it quickly became clear that they were two different crackers, separated by a thin layer of chocolate.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Good milk chocolate smell.

snack_name: Cadbury Dairy Milk Winter Wonderland Edition
snack_taste_test: Taste test: This large, thin chocolate bar had a novel design, with a pattern of Christmas trees alternating between milk chocolate and white chocolate trees, the milk chocolate ones being upside-down to allow this tessalation to work. There were three rows of trees, and each one had 6-1/2 trees of each type. The bottom of the bar was all milk chocolate, and when I broke off some sections, it was clear that the white parts were fairly thin relative to the bar (the label put the white chocolate at 12%).
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Intense chocolate smell, similar to other Cadbury bars.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This bar had five rectangular sections, each topped by the stylized Cadbury "C" design. The chocolate was a bit darker in color than most milk chocolate, but it was still far lighter dark chocolate.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Strong, rich milk chocolate smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This thick candy bar had an inside consisting of soft nougat on the top half and crisp rice held together by chocolate on the bottom half.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very rich chocolate smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This box contained many small, finger-shaped cookies coated in chocolate.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Good Cadbury chocolate smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This was basically a regular Flake bar dipped in milk chocolate, which acted like a chocolate shell for the inner Flake bar.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smells like chocolate.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This bar of chocolate had white chocolate "flakes" covered by a milk chocolate shell.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smelled like chocolate.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This bar was fairly typical in length, but it was very thin, promising to deliver fudge and milk chocolate.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Mild fudge smell. Nice.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This smallish bar had a flat bottom and a dome-shaped top, with bits of crushed peanut showing through the chocolate on top.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Great chocolate and peanut butter smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: The name pretty much said it all with these, as they were a larger version of Cadbury's milk chocolate Buttons, which are like nonpareils but without the white pieces stuck to one side.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Good milk chocolate smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This candy bar from South Africa had a lumpy-looking milk chocolate exterior, with a flat bottom, and it was fairly long at a bit over 5 inches
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very nice caramel, chocolate and peanuts smell. Mmmmmmm!

snack_taste_test: Taste test: Until I saw this box, I had never even heard of Cadbury making cookies, so I bought it mostly out of curiosity.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice dark chocolate chip cookies smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This thick candy bar had a roundish profile, except for a flat bottom.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Just an OK chocolate smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This candy bar lived up to its name in size, as it was indeed quite big, but it was not very dense and felt lighter than many much smaller candy bars.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Good caramel and milk chocolate smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This irregularly shaped bar was filled with lots of peanuts, some raisins and crisp rice, all held together by caramel, and then coated in milk chocolate.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very peanutty chocolate smell, and you can smell the raisins too.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This Halloween-themed version of the Cadbury Creme Egg had the same shape and milk chocolate exterior inside the foil wrapper, with some circles and patterns on the chocolate surfaces.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Good milk chocolate smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: When I saw the name of this candy bar, I loved the name, and I just knew that I had to buy it.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very strong, sweet milk chocolate smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This candy bar had an inside made of caramel and crunchy bits of peanuts, with a milk chocolate coating on the outside.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very sweet chocolatey smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This large, lumpy-looking Canadian candy bar consisted mostly of peanuts and chocolate, with lots of peanuts on the inside and a milk chocolate coating on the outside.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Lots of peanuts and chocolate smell. Very nice.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: Each of the two parallel bars in this Twix-like package consisted of two wafers with an airy chocolate truffle-like layer between them, with the whole thing coated in chocolate.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very sweet chocolate smell. Not that good.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This package had two thin bars in it, kind of like how they package Twix.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Sweet chocolate smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This chocolate bar was pretty thick at about 5/8 inch, and it was all one section, with a trapezoidal profile and a smooth top bearing no logos or writing.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice milk chocolate smell. Strong.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This fairly large candy bar contained caramel and peanut butter, plus scattered bits of peanuts and Rice Krispies, with a milk chocolate exterior.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Good, extra-sweet peanut butter and chocolate smell.

snack_name: Cape Cod 40% Reduced Fat Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: I could definitely notice the difference between the original Cape Cod chips and this 40% Reduced fat variety, as these were less greasy and a had a different kind of crunch (a slightly inferior one, but still good).
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Kind of an oily smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips had the golden yellow color that's typical of Cape Cod chips, with very wiggly shapes and small bubbles embedded inside, plus lots of skin along the edges and a smattering of dark seasoning powder.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice barbecue meat smell, just a bit smoky and slightly sweet.

snack_name: Cape Cod Beachside Barbecue Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These were pretty good barbecue chips.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Pretty good barbecue smell. Not sweet or hot.

snack_name: Cape Cod Buttermilk Ranch Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These kettle-cooked potato chips had a fair amount of flavor powder on them, with little green specks that made the chips look like sour cream and onion flavor.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Oddly, it smells like fried dough, or other smells you'd find at a local carnival.

snack_name: Cape Cod Cheddar Jack & Sour Cream Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These kettle-cooked chips were much like regular Cape Cod chips, but with a cheddar and sour cream taste.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Oily smell, like canola oil.

snack_name: Cape Cod Dark Russet Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are really great chips.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very nice, very potatoey smell, like a really good baked potato.

snack_name: Cape Cod Firecracker Barbecue Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: There are lots of barbecue chips out there, but most of them are pretty much the same.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very nice sweet barbecue smell.

snack_name: Cape Cod Golden Russett Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are a lot like the regular Cape Cod chips, but they're darker in color and they feel a bit drier in your mouth.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice, mild baked potato-like smell.

snack_name: Cape Cod Homestyle Potato Chips Cinnamon & Sugar Sweet Potato
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These sweet potato chips were large, dark, wiggly and seaoned fairly heavily with cinnamon sugar.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Mostly a strong sweet potato smell, quite good, with maybe a slight hint of cinnamon.

snack_name: Cape Cod Hot Air Popped Chocolate Caramel Popcorn
snack_taste_test: Taste test: It's hard to go wrong with any snack that starts with popcorn, covers it with caramel, and then covers it yet again with chocolate.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: A mild milk chocolate smell.

snack_name: Cape Cod Kettle Cooked Potato Chips Aged White Cheddar & Sour Cream
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips had wiggly shapes and a light yellow color, with a bit of whitish powder on the surfaces. There were some bubbles embedded into the chips, plus some darkish skin on parts of the edges.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Fairly strong kick of sour cream.

snack_name: Cape Cod Kettle Cooked Potato Chips Chef's Recipe Feta & Rosemary
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips were wiggly and pale yellow in color, with some large green specks distributed evenly over the chips.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Mild cheese and spices.

snack_name: Cape Cod Kettle Cooked Potato Chips Chef's Recipe Roasted Garlic & Red Pepper
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These chips looked like the original Cape Cod Potato Chips, with the same yellow color, wiggly shapes, bits of skin on the edges and dark spots here and there.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smells like roasted vegetables with maybe some vinegar. Pretty good.

snack_name: Cape Cod Kettle Cooked Potato Chips Harvest Gold
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips were wiggly and had a good yellow color, and I crunched in to find that they had a good crispness with a moderate level of crunch and sort of a bubbly surface texture.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very nice, similar to Russet potato chips, but sweeter. Great.

snack_name: Cape Cod Kettle Cooked Potato Chips Infused Fresh Jalapeño
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips generally came in small pieces, with some wiggly shapes and folded-over chips. The chips had a golden yellow color, but there were also many dark spots, particularly along the edges. There was no sign of anything green, which would be consistent with the bag's concept of the jalapeño flavor being in the oil, rather than in seasoning powder.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Mild jalapeno smell, not hot, but fresh.

snack_name: Cape Cod Kettle Cooked Potato Chips Infused Mediterranean
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips promised mix of spices that included basil, oregano and rosemary, but unlike most similarly flavored chips, they did it without any sort of seasoning on the surfaces. Instead, they somehow got the flavor there by infusing it into the oil. So the chips looked like ordinary potato chips, with the same nice golden color and wiggly shapes and Cape Cod's original chips.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice mix of spices, primarily Oregano.

snack_name: Cape Cod Kettle Cooked Potato Chips Limited Batch Asiago Cheese & Italian Herbs
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips came in generally smallish, wiggly pieces, with various shades of golden yellow on the surfaces. It felt like the surfaces had lots of seasoning, but most of the seasoning blended into the color of the chips, with the exception of a tiny amount of green specks.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Lots of cheese, lots of herbs. Really nice.

snack_name: Cape Cod Kettle Cooked Potato Chips Limited Batch Back Bay Crab Seasoning
snack_taste_test: Taste test: The chips in this bag had a golden yellow color overall, with some dark bits of seasoning distributed fairly evenly on the surfaces, plus some scattered dark bits of skin on the edges. Most of the chips were quite wiggly and fairly small, with some folded-over chips in the mix.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smells like Old Bay, but somewhat mild.

snack_name: Cape Cod Kettle Cooked Potato Chips Limited Batch Chipotle Barbeque
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips were generally small and came in wiggly shapes, with many folded-over chips, mostly smallish bubbles embedded inside, some dark skin on the edges and a fairly bright orange color overall.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Fairly typical barbecue chips smell.

snack_name: Cape Cod Kettle Cooked Potato Chips Limited Batch Honey & Dijon Mustard
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips had a strong yellow color, with wiggly shapes and many folded-over pieces.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice mustardy kick.

snack_name: Cape Cod Kettle Cooked Potato Chips Limited Batch Roasted Black Garlic
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips had the wiggly shapes and embedded bubbles that are typical of Cape Cod chips, with a nice golden yellow color and some bits of skin on the edges.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice, slightly sweet garlic smell.

snack_name: Cape Cod Kettle Cooked Potato Chips Limited Batch Smoked Gouda
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips had a pale yellow color generally, with very wiggly shapes and many bubbles embedded inside, plus areas of skin on the edges and occasional spots of browning. There wasn't any seasoning obviously visible, but a close look revealed some fine white powder that helped to make the chips look so pale.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Strong gouda smell.

snack_name: Cape Cod Kettle Cooked Potato Chips Limited Batch Sweet Red Chili
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips had a similar pale yellow color and wiggly shapes as we've come to expect from Cape Cod chips.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice mild sweet pepper smell.

snack_name: Cape Cod Kettle Cooked Potato Chips New England Bisque
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips had the usual yellow color and wiggly shapes of Cape Cod chips, with a smattering of green bits on the surfaces. As a New Englander, I found the "New England Bisque" name confusing, as it kind of implied lobster bisque or some other kind of seafood bisque, but it didn't actually say it. The ingredients didn't include any kind of seafood. But that sure looked like a picture of a lobster tail on the bag!
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Kind of remotely seafood-like, but not really like a seafood bisque.

snack_name: Cape Cod Kettle Cooked Potato Chips Pink Himalayan Salt & Red Wine Vinegar
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips looked much like the original Cape Cod potato chips, with the same wiggly shapes and golden yellow colors. When I grabbed my first chip, I could feel some powder on the surfaces.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very mild vinegar smell.

snack_name: Cape Cod Kettle Cooked Potato Chips Russet
snack_taste_test: Taste test: Cape Cod's Dark Russet Potato Chips were long a favorite of many snackers, including us, but they've been absent from snack-aisle shelves for a number of years, along with other Cape Cod russet chips: Robust Russet, Golden Russet and Golden Russet Waves. But this time, as the bag declared, "You asked. It's back!" it was away with the adjectives and back to the basics, just "Russet."
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Good strong Russet potato smell.

snack_name: Cape Cod Kettle Cooked Potato Chips Waffle Cut Barbeque Ranch
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These chips used the same cross-cut technique of as Cape Cod's other recent varieties (Sea Salt, Seasoned Pepper, Buffalo Cheddar and Farm Stand Ranch), giving them the same excellent texture, with good crispness and a more solid crunch than regular ripple chips.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very mild. One hint each of barbecue and ranch, nothing intense.

snack_name: Cape Cod Kettle Cooked Waffle Cut Potato Chips Buffalo Cheddar
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips had the same type of opposing-angle cut as Cape Cod's other waffle-cut varieties, but with also some orange seasoning in this case, as well as some dark bits of skin around the edges.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smells almost like raw potatoes. Not like Buffalo sauce.

snack_name: Cape Cod Kettle Cooked Waffle Cut Potato Chips Farm Stand Ranch
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips had the extra-crunchy cross-cut ripples that Cape Cod perfected for some other flavors, with a bit of seasoning, some fine white powder in the crevices, plus some small green and red seasoning bits.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Strong veggies and ranch smell, could especially notice the celery.

snack_name: Cape Cod Kettle Cooked Waffle Cut Potato Chips Sea Salt
snack_taste_test: Taste test: Within the potato chips category, it's rare to see much in the way of true innovation, especially with regard to shapes or recipes (though we often find innovative flavors).
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Mild potato smell.

snack_name: Cape Cod Kettle Cooked Waffle Cut Potato Chips Seasoned Pepper
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips brought the new waffle cut that we first tried in Cape Cod's sea salt flavor to the world of black pepper chips, and our tasters were quite thrilled with the results.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smelled like a baked potato with plenty of black pepper.

snack_name: Cape Cod Kettle Style Whole Grain Chips Toasted Grains
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These chips looked like a knockoff of Sun Chips, and they indeed followed a similar multigrain concept, in this case combining corn, wheat and oats into a beige-colored, wavy chip.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Kind of like Sun Chips.

snack_name: Cape Cod Nantucket Spice Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are typical Cape Cod chips (meaning they are the standard which all other kettle chips shall be judged -- in other words, they're good chips) with the added bonus of having a salt and pepper type of taste.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: It has an aroma, but we can't place it. Slight spice aroma.

snack_name: Cape Cod No Salt Added Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These have the same look and texture as the regular Cape Cod chips.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smells good, the same as the regular Cape Cod chips.

snack_name: Cape Cod Old Fashioned Kettle-Cooked Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are really good chips.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Kind of like raw potatoes, but with some saltiness.

snack_name: Cape Cod Potato Chips Five Cheese
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips had the same sorts of wiggly, irregular shapes that we've come to expect from Cape Cod chips, and they also had lots of orange-colored seasoning on them — not nearly as bright orange as, say, Cheetos, but still very orange, about the same as the orange used on most of the front of the bag.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice mild mix of cheeses

snack_name: Cape Cod Potato Chips Jalapeño & Aged Cheddar
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are very good chips.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Mildly strong jalapeno smell with even milder cheese. Good.

snack_name: Cape Cod Potato Chips Parmesan & Roasted Garlic
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These pale yellow potato chips were somewhat wiggly and had some whitish seasoning visible on their surfaces, along with some green specks.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Garlicy and parmesany but nothing special.

snack_name: Cape Cod Potato Chips Sea Salt & Cracked Pepper
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These chips were crunchy and had a nice peppery taste, with maybe a slight cheese flavor mixed in, a nice taste.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice, sharp peppery smell.

snack_name: Cape Cod Potato Chips Thins Original
snack_taste_test: Taste test: Since this was the second flavor from Cape Cod's new Thins line of potato chips that we reviewed, there was less mystery surrounding it than the initial one, Smokey Barbecue. But it turned out that there was still major element of surprise in this bag.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice strong, rich potato smell.

snack_name: Cape Cod Potato Chips Thins Smokey Barbecue
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips had a nice light orange low, with some sparse bits of darkish seasoning on the surfaces, plus some bubbles embedded inside and occasional bits of skin on the edges. I crunched in to find that they lacked the crunchy, kettle-cooked feel of most Cape Cod chips. They were still nicely crisp (indeed, even crisper) but they had a softer crunch.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Good potato smell, very mild on the barbecue.

snack_name: Cape Cod Potato Chips Whole Earth Collection Robust Russet
snack_taste_test: Taste test: I've never been a big fan of russet-style chips, they always look burned to me and they taste kind of odd.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: A deep, earthy type of aroma.

snack_name: Cape Cod Premium White Cheddar Cheese Popcorn
snack_taste_test: Taste test: This is really good white cheddar popcorn with a teriffic and addictive cheddar taste.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice cheddar cheese aroma, with the cheddar aroma overpowering the popcorn aroma.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are pretzels shaped like lighthouses.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: The regulal pretzels smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These cheese puffs had shapes that looked a lot like Puffcorn, which is to say, shaped kind of remotely like popcorn, but not really, and bigger. They had an off-white color.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Strong cheese smell, too strong.

snack_name: Cape Cod Reduced Fat Fresh Garden Herb Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips had a kettle-cooked texture similar to other Cape Cod chips, with a pretty good herb flavoring.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Pretty good herb smell.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This bag was filled just over halfway with generally white kernels that had just a very light smattering of a caramel-looking seasoning. The color of the seasoning was fairly light, and we had to look very closely to even see it.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice mild caramel smell.

snack_name: Cape Cod Sea Salt and Vinegar Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are good.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Wow, quite a vinegar zing.

snack_name: Cape Cod Shapes of the Cape 25% Reduced Fat Baked Snack Crackers Sharp Cheddar
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These crackers were a lot like Cheez-Its in terms of taste and texture.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very cheesy smell.

snack_name: Cape Cod Shapes of the Cape Baked Snack Crackers Smoked Cheddar
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are small, hollow crackers shaped like various things you might see on Cape Cod: a lighthouse, sailboat, seagull and scallop shell.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very nice bacony cheddar aroma.

snack_name: Cape Cod Sour Cream and Chives Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are really good.
snack_smell_test: From the package:  “We flavor these special chips with our own blend that is reminiscent of a perfectly seasoned baked potato.”

snack_name: Cape Cod Summer Cracked Pepper and a Hint of Lemon Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips were generally quite small and had wiggly shapes with a light yellow color plus a smattering of fine black seasoning, plus lots of dark skin around the edges.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice smell, slightly citrusy, but couldn't notice the black pepper.

snack_name: Cape Cod Sweet & Spicy Jalapeño Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: Cape Cod's take on the jalapeno potato chip was quite a bit different from the many other jalapeno chips we've tried. They loaded their crunchy, wiggly kettle-cooked chips up with a mix of spices that were quite tasty (and somewhat hot) for a great taste.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very nice! Not just jalapeno heat, but a great combination of jalapeno, potato and spices. Wow.

snack_name: Cape Cod Sweet Mesquite Barbeque Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These kettle-cooked chips had a lot of color to them, a deep and dark orange, with additional darker flecks of flavoring.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: There was a barbecue smell, but it was a deeper aroma rather than a barbecue sauce-like smell. But it didn't seem to smell like wood smoke or mesquite either.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These large tortilla chips came in three different earth-tone colors and tasted good, with more of a mixed vegetable taste than any specific vegetables standing out.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: A lot like the typical veggie chips smell, but with some corn tortilla mixed in too. Pretty good.

snack_name: Cape Cod Tortilla Dipping Shells Ancient Grain Quinoa, Black Sesame & Amaranth
snack_taste_test: Taste test: Cape Cod's version of the dipping-optimized tortilla chip had simpler shapes than the many-sided Tostitos Scoops, with the round tortilla folded upward on four sides, at most. It's "at most" because the shapes varied from chip to chip, with some only having two or three of those four positions bent that way.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Much sweeter than your typical tortilla chips.

snack_name: Cape Cod Tortilla Dipping Shells Four Bean Black, Pinto, Red & Adzuki Beans
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These tortilla chips had somewhat irregular dippable shapes, much like the Ancient Grains version, but in this case the color of the chips was just light beige and not yellow at all, with lots of black spots.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Kind of a mix of salty tortilla chips and beans Pretty good.

snack_name: Cape Cod Waves 40% Reduced Fat Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are rippled potato chips made by the Cape Cod potato chip company.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: They smell like a normal bag of potato chips.

snack_name: Cape Cod Waves 40% Reduced Fat Sea Salt
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These wide-rippled potato chips had a yellow color generally, with some darker areas, and they came in lots of different shapes and sizes.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice rich potato smell.

snack_name: Cape Cod Waves Golden Russett Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These wide-rippled, kettle-cooked chips are very, very crunchy and taste quite good.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very, very nice russet potato smell.

snack_name: Cape Cod Waves Kettle Cooked White Cheddar & Sour Cream
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These potato chips had wide, shallow ripples and fairly irregular shapes, some folded-over, with a strong yellow color and many areas of browning.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Strong cheddary potato flavor. OK.

snack_name: Cape Cod Wavy Cut Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: I was very skeptical about these chips, as wavy cut chips in the past have been disappointing, a poor replacement for chips with narrower ripples.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: A really cool smell — the bag smelled like the fried dough stand at a state fair or carnival.

snack_name: Cape Cod White Corn Tortilla Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are really good tortilla chips.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Regular tortilla chips aroma.

snack_name: Cape Cod Whole Earth Collection 40% Reduced Fat Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are good kettle-style chips.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Regular kettle chips smell.

snack_name: Cape Cod Whole Earth Collection All Natural Blue Corn with Sesame Tortilla Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are excellent tortilla chips.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: A bit different than regular tortilla chips. You can smell the sesame.

snack_name: Cape Cod Whole Earth Collection All Natural Garlic & Herb White Corn Tortilla Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are very good tortilla chips.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Wow, a great, mildly garlicy aroma.

snack_name: Cape Cod Whole Earth Collection Classic Lightly Salted Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are excellent chips.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very nice, mild fried potato smell.

snack_name: Cape Cod Whole Earth Collection Classic Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are good chips.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice light, potatoey smell.

snack_name: Cape Cod Whole Earth Collection Sea Salt Popcorn
snack_taste_test: Taste test: This is really good popcorn, with a nice, light salty taste.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smells like buttered corn on the cob.

snack_name: Cape Cod Whole Earth Collection Sierra Gold Homestyle Potato Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: This variety of Cape Cod Potato Chips different greatly from what we've come to expect from Cape Cod.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Standard salted potato chips smell, not the kettle-cooked potato chips smell that I would expect from Cape Cod chips.

snack_name: Cape Cod Whole Earth Collection White Corn Tortilla Chips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are good tortilla chips.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very rich tortilla chips smell. Good.

snack_name: Cape Cod Yellow Corn Tortilla Strips
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These tortilla chips are rectangular in shape and resemble overside Fritos.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Sort of like corn, but not that good.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These thick granola bars consisted mostly of oats and Rice Krispies inside, with a sprinkling of white frosting on top and a coating of caramel on the bottom.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Strong coffee smell. Sweet too.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This was similar in composition to your typical granola bar, as it consisted primary of oats and crisp rice.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Strong coffee smell. Nice.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These bars had a center that looked like your typical crisp rice and oats-based granola bar, except with a chocolate coating on the bottom and a single squiggle of very light green-colored frosting on top (less frosting than it shows in the picture).
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very nice, a mix of coffee, mint and chocolate.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: Chester Cheetah has gone the baked route, along with many other snacks in the Frito-Lay line, including Doritos, Lay's and Ruffles.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Mmmmmm ... cheesy.

snack_name: Baked Cheetos Crunchy 100 Calorie Mini Bites
snack_taste_test: Taste test: This version of Crunchy Cheetos consisted of smaller cheese curls than the usual kind, as the smaller pieces let them up the number of Cheetos while still staying within 100 calorie limit.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smells like Cheetos.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These Cheetos had an impressively bright glow from the red flavor powder on them.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Not much. Not like a cheese puff or hot sauce.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This version of Cheetos, packaged in a bag similar to the ones used in the 80s/90s, seemed just as cheesy as the current Cheetos Crunchy, despite the extra hyphen in the name. Our tasters really devoured the crunchy curls, getting all manner of orange powder all over their fingers (not to mention faces and clothes) in the process.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Very cheesy.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: Nearly eight years after reviewing a throwback edition of Crunchy Cheetos, there's finally a corresponding Puffs version. I don't think the bag was completely authentic (there are some modern labeling requirement to be met), but in addition to the old Chee-tos logo, the bag had the early version of Chester Cheetah and the pre-1997 Frito-Lay logo. And the words "Dangerously Cheesy" were nowhere to be found!
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Nice cheese smell, but not very strong.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These cheese puffs from Brazil were somewhat thin and had a pale orange (just about yellow) color. Most of the pieces were about 2 inches long and had fairly minimal curvature.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Slightly too strong cheese smell, but not too bad.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: This version of Cheetos looked kind of like crinkle-cut fries, with some general curvature as well for most pieces (much like the old-school Cheetos Zigzags), showing a yellow color overall and hints of orange. The flavor translated variously as cottage cheese or creamy cheese (all within the Google Translate app, depending on different combinations of words).
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Wow, really does smell like cottage cheese.

snack_taste_test: Taste test: These mini cheese puff balls were smaller than your average spherical cheese puff.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smells like a bag of Cheetos.

snack_name: Cheetos Bacon Cheddar Cheese Flavored Crackers
snack_taste_test: Taste test: These are pretty good crackers.
snack_smell_test: Smell test: Smells like bacon with cheddar cheese. Good.

snack_name: Cheetos Bag of Bones Flamin' Hot
snack_taste_test: Taste test: It's that time of year when many snacks appear on store shelves with special features for Halloween, and we're glad that Cheetos chief Chester Cheetah is playing the game. This one took the white cheddar version of Bag of Bones that we've seen in past years and swapped out the seasoning for the Flamin' Hot stuff.
